div.p:
My reply to the stupid cruel and largely truthless report of the three [persons], who sat anno dei 1871 to judge on her Majestys bot Garden of Victoria, has not yet been printed;

For the reply see M to C Duffy, 6 February 1872. M later sent a manuscript copy to Kew (RGB, Kew Misc. Reports, Melbourne, Mueller). No contemporary published version of the full response has been found, but it is summarized in newspaper reports of a meeting between the Minister of Lands, M and Ferguson, e.g. Daily telegraph (Melbourne), 12 July 1872, p. 3. See also Maroske & Cohn (1996). 
                but when issued you surely shall have a copy. So you may see, what it means when proverbially it has become said "what may happen to a man in Victoria"
